net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.variables

Class ArrayAccess

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Node
      • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Value
        • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Identifier
          • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.variables.Variable
            • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.variables.ArrayAccess

  • public class ArrayAccess
extends Variable
    Value extension that keeps track of any time an array is being accessed. For example, the statement: "args[34]" is an array access. Obviously the previous code segment does nothing, however these nodes will be intertwined with method calls, assignments, if statements, etc.

      • getNumDimensions

        public int getNumDimensions()
        Get the number of dimensions that this node contains.

        For example: 
         int i[][][] = new int[5][4][3];
        The above array has three dimensions. In general, the number of dimensions relates to the number of sets of brackets there are contained within the array declaration.
        Returns:
        The number of dimensions that this node contains.

      • generateCUseOutput

        public java.lang.StringBuilder generateCUseOutput(java.lang.StringBuilder builder)
        Description copied from class: Identifier
        Generate the representation of when the variable is being used, in action, rather than being declared.

        For example:
         Person p;
 p.getName();
        The first line shows the declaration of the Variable. The second line demonstrates a "variable use" for the "p" variable. Essentially, the "variable use" output is exactly what it says, what the variable looks like when it is being used to do something.
        Overrides:
        generateCUseOutput in class Identifier
        Returns:
        What the variable looks like when it is being used to do something.

      • decodeStatement

        public static ArrayAccess decodeStatement(Node parent,
                          java.lang.String statement,
                          Location location,
                          boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into an ArrayAccess if possible. If it is not possible, the method will return null.

        An example input would be: "args[34]"
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a ArrayAccess instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a ArrayAccess.
